sirocco
------------------------------------------
This is a library for computing homotopy continuation of a given root of one
dimensional sections of bivariate complex polynomials. The output is a
piecewise linear approximation of the path followed by the root, with the
property that there is a tubular neighborhood, with square transversal
section, that contains the actual path, and there is a three times thicker
tubular neighborhood guaranted to contain no other root of the polynomial.
This second property ensures that the piecewise linear approximation computed
from all roots of a polynomial form a topologically correct deformation of the
actual braid, since the inner tubular neighborhoods cannot intersect.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.6.6-1
  libgcc1-13.4.0-1
  libmpfr6-4.2.2-1
  libsirocco-devel-2.1.1-1bl1
  libsirocco0-2.1.1-1bl1
  libstdc++6-13.4.0-1
  pkg-config-2.5.1-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-15-2
  automake-20250528-1
  binutils-2.45.1-1
  cygport-0.37.6-1
  gcc-core-13.4.0-1
  gcc-g++-13.4.0-1
  libmpfr-devel-4.2.2-1
  libtool-2.5.4-1
  make-4.4.1-2

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/miguelmarco/SIROCCO2

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/miguelmarco/SIROCCO2/archive/refs/tags/2.1.1.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack sirocco-2.1.1-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./sirocco-2.1.1-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/sirocco-2.1.1-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/sirocco-2.1.1-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libsirocco0-2.1.1-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libsirocco-devel-2.1.1-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(sirocco)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/sirocco.README
  /usr/share/doc/sirocco/LICENSE
  /usr/share/doc/sirocco/README.md

(libsirocco0)
  /usr/bin/cygsirocco-0.dll

(libsirocco-devel)
  /usr/include/sirocco.h
  /usr/lib/libsirocco.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/libsirocco.pc

